_source.message:
Handle releases tarballs that contain files in unsorted order

Releases created on Mac OS have their files in arbitrary order.
This makes fast unpack on Linux to fail find all jobs in release.
Validate that all release jobs were unpacked after fast unpack. If
not fall back to slow unpack.

[#111654976](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/111654976)

Signed-off-by: Mikhail Vyshegorodtsev <mvyshegorodtse@vmware.com>
_source.message_analyzed:
Handle releases tarballs that contain files in unsorted order

Releases created on Mac OS have their files in arbitrary order.
This makes fast unpack on Linux to fail find all jobs in release.
Validate that all release jobs were unpacked after fast unpack. If
not fall back to slow unpack.

[#111654976](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/111654976)

Signed-off-by: Mikhail Vyshegorodtsev <mvyshegorodtse@vmware.com>

_source.message:
Remove extra settings fetching

* Vsphere CPI connects CDROM only when settings are
updated. Since we eject CDROM after settings are fetched
we can't read settings again. Only load settings when
calling LoadSettings (bootstrap, mount).

* Do not get settings twice when detecting selected source.

* Public SSH key multi source gets the key from whatever
source succeeds.

Signed-off-by: Mehran Saliminia <msaliminia@gmail.com>
_source.message_analyzed:
Remove extra settings fetching

* Vsphere CPI connects CDROM only when settings are
updated. Since we eject CDROM after settings are fetched
we can't read settings again. Only load settings when
calling LoadSettings (bootstrap, mount).

* Do not get settings twice when detecting selected source.

* Public SSH key multi source gets the key from whatever
source succeeds.

Signed-off-by: Mehran Saliminia <msaliminia@gmail.com>
_source.title: Remove extra settings fetching

_source.message:
Remove error when multiple dynamic networks provided

If we have several dynamic/manual networks and at least one of them is
without MAC address we cannot determine which network should be resolved.
Current implementation naively checks just for multiple dynamic networks.
Instead delegate to InterfaceConfigurationCreator to handle multiple
networks without MAC address (fail).

Signed-off-by: Maria Shaldibina <mshaldibina@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Remove error when multiple dynamic networks provided

If we have several dynamic/manual networks and at least one of them is
without MAC address we cannot determine which network should be resolved.
Current implementation naively checks just for multiple dynamic networks.
Instead delegate to InterfaceConfigurationCreator to handle multiple
networks without MAC address (fail).

Signed-off-by: Maria Shaldibina <mshaldibina@pivotal.io>
_source.title: Remove error when multiple dynamic networks provided

_source.message:
All network reservation are handled in instance

In case if there is a VM without an instance we don't
need to release network reservations for that VM. We used to reserve
network reservations first, which required as to release them for
non-global-network case. In global network case there should not be any
reservations in DB that belong to VM without an instance.

[#99270966](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/99270966)

Signed-off-by: Xuebin He <xuebin.he@emc.com>
_source.message_analyzed:
All network reservation are handled in instance

In case if there is a VM without an instance we don't
need to release network reservations for that VM. We used to reserve
network reservations first, which required as to release them for
non-global-network case. In global network case there should not be any
reservations in DB that belong to VM without an instance.

[#99270966](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/99270966)

Signed-off-by: Xuebin He <xuebin.he@emc.com>
_source.title: All network reservation are handled in instance

_source.message:
Package compilation happens before VM IPs are reserved

We don't need as many IPs available now. Some integration tests changed
because the InMemoryIpProvider allocates the oldest released IPs first
(so the compilation VM IP that gets released isn't the one that gets
 used for the instance VM).

[finishes #97926768](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/97926768)
[#95199966](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/95199966)

Signed-off-by: Colin Obyrne <cobyrne@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Package compilation happens before VM IPs are reserved

We don't need as many IPs available now. Some integration tests changed
because the InMemoryIpProvider allocates the oldest released IPs first
(so the compilation VM IP that gets released isn't the one that gets

[finishes #97926768](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/97926768)
[#95199966](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/95199966)

_source.title: Package compilation happens before VM IPs are reserved

_source.message:
InMemoryProvider allows to reserve unresolved reservations

InMemoryProvider constructs the list of reserved IPs every time
from scratch. Because of that we need to call reserve IP for existing
instance. Check if IP was not resolved before raising AlreadyReserved
error to handle existing instance case.

Signed-off-by: Xuebin He <xuebin.he@emc.com>
_source.message_analyzed:
InMemoryProvider allows to reserve unresolved reservations

InMemoryProvider constructs the list of reserved IPs every time
from scratch. Because of that we need to call reserve IP for existing
instance. Check if IP was not resolved before raising AlreadyReserved
error to handle existing instance case.

Signed-off-by: Xuebin He <xuebin.he@emc.com>
_source.title: InMemoryProvider allows to reserve unresolved reservations

Lock down json gem version in bosh release

Instances are reused when rebalancing vms accross AZs

[#99740226](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/99740226)

Indexes of reused instances are preserved to prevent
health monitor deeming the reused instances are invalid.
New instances are assigned the lowest possible unused indexes.

_source.message:
Eliminates race conditions when deleting PTR records

When deleting a DNS A record, it would mistakenly delete not only
its PTR records but potentially the PTR records of other A records
that shared the same IP address.

This fix exclusively deletes the PTR record(s) associated with the specified
domain/hostname pattern; it does not delete others' PTR records.

[#108476894](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/108476894)

Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Eliminates race conditions when deleting PTR records

_source.message:
upgrade rubocop to work with ruby 2.3

[#117398595](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/117398595)

We need to upgrade RuboCop so that it can parse Ruby 2.3 code. Unfortunately
there have been some changes to the names of the linting rules which meant that
our library of RuboCop configuration was out of date and required substantial
changes. This was too much work so I deleted all of them and replaced it with a
single file listing the rules that are failing across the entire project.

Some of these look like they're actually exposing bugs. Some of them are less
important. Now the list is manageable we can see the problems and fix them.

Signed-off-by: Christopher Brown <cbrown@pivotal.io>
Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>

_source.message:
Create tombstones after deleting records to avoid a race

- If tombstones are inserted before deletion and another thread
publishes dns records, they will contain the soon-to-be-deleted record,
and the inconsistency will not be fixed until the version changes a
second time (i.e. a record is created or deleted)

[#142167931](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/142167931)

Signed-off-by: Tom Viehman <tviehman@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Create tombstones after deleting records to avoid a race

- If tombstones are inserted before deletion and another thread
publishes dns records, they will contain the soon-to-be-deleted record,
and the inconsistency will not be fixed until the version changes a
second time (i.e. a record is created or deleted)

[#142167931](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/142167931)

Signed-off-by: Tom Viehman <tviehman@pivotal.io>
_source.title: Create tombstones after deleting records to avoid a race

_source.message:
Convert non-ASCII errand output for non-utf8 mysql

We should only strip characters if the original data fails to be
inserted correctly, based on known errors related to character set and
collation misconfigurations. Future story (#147467271) will try to ensure
mysql tables are always created with the appropraite settings, regardless
of default database settings.

[#147533883](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/147533883)

Signed-off-by: Danny Berger <dberger@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:

_source.message:
Fix deadlock in errand parallel step spec

- ConditionVariable#signal only wakes up threads that are running
`resource.wait` before `signal` is called. Before this we had a change
of calling `wait` after `signal` causing a deadlock.
- Replace ConditionVariable usage in tests with Thread::Queue

[#151526938](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/151526938)

Signed-off-by: Luan Santos <lsantos@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Fix deadlock in errand parallel step spec

- ConditionVariable#signal only wakes up threads that are running
`resource.wait` before `signal` is called. Before this we had a change
of calling `wait` after `signal` causing a deadlock.
- Replace ConditionVariable usage in tests with Thread::Queue

[#151526938](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/151526938)

Signed-off-by: Luan Santos <lsantos@pivotal.io>
_source.title: Fix deadlock in errand parallel step spec

_source.message:
Revert "Integration tests for bosh-cli vms --cloud-properties"

It seems like we are not passing the `vm_resources` option to
`simple_manifest_with_instance_groups_and_vm_resources`, but it also is
not accounting for `vm_type` and `vm_resources` being mutually
exclusive.

Tests are currently failing...

     # https://main.bosh-ci.cf-app.com/teams/main/pipelines/bosh:cli/jobs/integration-2.3-postgres-gocli/builds/994
     Failure/Error: expect(vms.map { |vm| vm[:cloud_properties]}).to eq([cloud_props_from_dummy_cpi, cloud_props_from_dummy_cpi, cloud_props_from_dummy_cpi])

       expected: ["ephemeral_disk:\n  size: 10\ninstance_type: dummy", "ephemeral_disk:\n  size: 10\ninstance_type: dummy", "ephemeral_disk:\n  size: 10\ninstance_type: dummy"]
            got: ["", "", ""]

       (compared using ==)

       Diff:
       @@ -1,4 +1 @@
       -ephemeral_disk:\n  size: 10\ninstance_type: dummy
       -ephemeral_disk:\n  size: 10\ninstance_type: dummy
       -ephemeral_disk:\n  size: 10\ninstance_type: dummy

     # ./spec/gocli/integration/cli_vms_spec.rb:43:in `block (2 levels) in <top (required)>'

This reverts commit a1cb7aa5f00512f52fdf3e41a3ae942cea07bca3.

[#151157765](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/151157765)

Signed-off-by: Kai Hofstetter <kai.hofstetter@sap.com>
_source.message_analyzed:

_source.message:
Fix broken migration

A migration, originally released in 257.x was updated in 258.x. The
update added an index to the local_dns_blobs table. Directors that have
been upgraded from 257 will not have this index. Therefore, the
update_sha1_column_sizes migration breaks when it tries to drop the
missing index. Furthermore we have deeemed the we do not need the index.
Hence we have decided to drop adding it back. A subsequent migration
will remove the index if it exists. This should address directors that
successfully ran the update_sha1_column_sizes migration before this fix.

[#140068815](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/140068815)

Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:

of /var/vcap/data/root_log when it is bind mounted.

_source.message:
Ignore VMNotFound errors when deleting VMs during deploy

- cloud.Error constants need to be Bosh::Clouds::* instead of
  Bosh::Cloud::*
- cloud.cpi_command_runner needs to not return an error unless it failed
  to shell out -- CPI errors are already in the CmdResult, and
  cloud.cloud is relying on pulling errors out of the CmdResult to
  return a cloud.Error to its caller.

[fixes #93732046]

Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Ignore VMNotFound errors when deleting VMs during deploy

- cloud.Error constants need to be Bosh::Clouds::* instead of
  Bosh::Cloud::*
- cloud.cpi_command_runner needs to not return an error unless it failed
  to shell out -- CPI errors are already in the CmdResult, and
  cloud.cloud is relying on pulling errors out of the CmdResult to
  return a cloud.Error to its caller.

[fixes #93732046]

Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>
_source.title: Ignore VMNotFound errors when deleting VMs during deploy

_source.message:
Compile and install packages from supplied releases
- no longer uses the pre-compiled packages in the stemcell blobstore
- resolve job package dependencies, including transitive package dependencies
- upload source package tarballs to the configured blobstore
- compile resolved job package dependencies
- compilation happens on the vm, in order to match OS & architecture
- compilation happens is serial, because there's only one vm

[#83805390]

Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Compile and install packages from supplied releases
- no longer uses the pre-compiled packages in the stemcell blobstore
- resolve job package dependencies, including transitive package dependencies
- upload source package tarballs to the configured blobstore
- compile resolved job package dependencies
- compilation happens on the vm, in order to match OS & architecture
- compilation happens is serial, because there's only one vm

[#83805390]

Signed-off-by: Tyler Schultz <tschultz@pivotal.io>

_source.message:
updating machines of a job with multiple azs should not affect multiple azs at once

The code is more complex than strictly necessary to accommodate
Dmitriy's concern that Hashes aren't necessarily enumerated properly
JRuby, for example, may not adhere to the official Ruby docs.
http://ruby-doc.org/core-1.9.3/Hash.html

Hashes enumerate their values in the order that the corresponding keys
were inserted.

Signed-off-by: Danny Berger <dberger@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
updating machines of a job with multiple azs should not affect multiple azs at once

The code is more complex than strictly necessary to accommodate
Dmitriy's concern that Hashes aren't necessarily enumerated properly
JRuby, for example, may not adhere to the official Ruby docs.
http://ruby-doc.org/core-1.9.3/Hash.html

Hashes enumerate their values in the order that the corresponding keys
were inserted.

Signed-off-by: Danny Berger <dberger@pivotal.io>
_source.title: updating machines of a job with multiple azs should not affect multiple azs at once

_source.message:
Remove vm_type_changed? check in favor of cloud_properties_changed?

The agent needs updating/vm needs recreating only when the vm_type
cloud properties have changed. When the vm_type name changes, it should
not recreate the vm, but instead update the database with the vm_type
name used during the last deploy.

[#109851192](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/109851192)

Signed-off-by: Danny Berger <dberger@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Remove vm_type_changed? check in favor of cloud_properties_changed?

The agent needs updating/vm needs recreating only when the vm_type

not recreate the vm, but instead update the database with the vm_type

[#109851192](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/109851192)

_source.message:
Installation targets are method parameters not constructor args

Getting the target when we construct the installers is too soon -- it
causes an empty state file to get written if none exists and prevents
bosh-init delete from exiting early.

[#97138492](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/97138492)

Signed-off-by: Colin Obyrne <cobyrne@pivotal.io>
_source.message_analyzed:
Installation targets are method parameters not constructor args

Getting the target when we construct the installers is too soon -- it
causes an empty state file to get written if none exists and prevents
bosh-init delete from exiting early.

[#97138492](https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/97138492)

Signed-off-by: Colin Obyrne <cobyrne@pivotal.io>
_source.title: Installation targets are method parameters not constructor args

Loosen kernel version path selection in spec

fixes:
```
CentOS 7 OS image installed by system_initramfs Command "zcat /boot/initramfs-3.10.0-514.6.1.el7.x86_64.img | cpio -t | grep '/lib/modules/3.10.0-514.6.1.el7.x86_64'" stdout should match /\/ata_generic\.ko/
```
